underlying_goal: Refactor a script for closing Mac apps to support two different whitelists: one for apps to not touch at all, and one for apps where only windows are closed.
primary_success: Successfully refactored the script to use efficient associative arrays for lookups instead of a verbose function, based on code-reviewer feedback.
brief_summary: User requested a two-tier whitelist for a Mac app cleanup script. Claude implemented the feature, then improved the implementation by using a `.conf` file and associative arrays for O(1) lookups after consulting a code-reviewer agent. The final, more efficient script was committed and pushed.
